messages.message: is there something happening with build cypress tests that they get cut off while naming the project...?
i’ve been seeing this last week as well… :disappointed:
we definitely should look into this :confused:
some of my CI runs have also failed bc of this :confused_dog:

in this CI run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/10692/test-results/8b03160e-8003-44b3-a89a-db8df0128287/replay?actions=%5B%5D&att=1&browsers=%5B%5D&groups=%5B%5D&isFlaky=%5B%5D&modificationDateRange=%7B%22startDate%22%3A%221970-01-01%22%2C%22endDate%22%3A%222038-01-19%22%7D&orderBy=EXECUTION_ORDER&oses=%5B%5D&pc=log-https%3A%2F%2Fcrafting-aihub--pr-58134-instabase.instabase.site.sandboxes.run-569__command-logs&specs=%5B%5D&statuses=%5B%5D&testingTypesEnum=%5B%5D&ts=1717204545269.7), the renaming failed bc the typing action didn’t go through

somehow a failure to get the project docs affected the typing action in Cypress?
if it defocuses the typing that could happen
hmmmm i think these projects were all caused by the Cypress runs on my PR https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58134
turns out that my changes cause a “Failed to load documents” toast to appear on every empty Build project -> this likely interrupts the typing action when renaming a Build project

hmm i take it back, some of them are caused by my PR’s CI runs (ex: https://crafting-aihub.test.instabase.com/build/018fd0e5-39c5-7569-9599-13ac9dc2b2c5), but not all (ex: https://crafting-aihub.test.instabase.com/build/2bba2410-886b-4b40-b1fe-551d2b39e97d)
@danny.lan i’ll try changing `project-cleanup` then in this problematic PR
